If you like understanding business processes, helping to design solutions, working with a wide range of people and delivering results that matter, this is an opportunity for you. As a SAP BI Functional Analyst (BIA) in Information Technology you will work with cross functional teams, to create analytic capability, providing decision makers with actionable business intelligence. You will partner closely with Business and IT functional teams to understand business process learn the data and craft solutions to solve problems. 
You will work with architects and engineers to model data that can deliver answers to business questions and fit within a strategic direction for architecture. You will have the opportunity to work on strategic BI initiatives that are driven from Micronâ€™s business strategy and have an immediate impact to customers. This role will work closely with Sales and Supply Chain. 
This position requires cross functional coordination, outstanding communication skills, creative problem solving and a highly organized, process-focused aptitude to manage a variety of responsibilities and deliverables. In this role, you will have the opportunity to utilize your passion for technology and business process excellence. Position will be located in Boise, Idaho. 
 
Responsibilities include: 
Lead BI Solution lifecycle through requirement gathering, analysis, design, data-modeling, testing and deployment 
Architect, design and prototype solutions to support business strategies and deliver business value 
Communicate with users to ensure BI deliverables are providing business value 
Work with end users and IT teams to resolve operational issues and mitigate risk 
Help business users leverage the appropriate BI techniques and tools 
Work with project teams to document business requirements definitions, including business opportunity, vision of solution and expected benefits 
Review project success criteria ensuring deliverable and stakeholder alignment 
Build relationships with business areas, understand their commitments, establish trust and dialogue on how to support those commitments 
Perform impact analysis and gap analysis to create data flow diagrams that support key business process and information capabilities 
Work with the Business area subject matter experts to learn the data and understand how it is used by various areas supporting business process 
 
Qualifications and Experience: 
Minimum of 6 yearsâ€™ work experience in Business Intelligence 
A passion for data and information 
